Joins

1. Inner Join
To fetch common records btw 2 tables , table A has Pk reference and B has FK reference
Result : Only the common details btw A&B
A -> Left Table
B-> Right Table


2. Left Join
Results : All records of left table and the common cols btw A & B
Film and film category and category ,  customer and rental 


3. Right Join 
Results : All records of right table and the common cols btw A & B



4. Full Outer Join
Result : Fetch all records from A , B and also the common cols



5. Full outer join with A.key or B.key is Null
Results: Only cols of A& B , but not the common cols



6. Cross Join or Cartesian Join
We apply a cartesian product
3 Records in Table A , 3 Records in Table B 
Then the result will have 3*3 = 9 results.


7. Self Join
Staff table



--> Normalization Concepts
--> Union
--> Where exists


























